ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Overall, did you like the My Health Coach app?
Notes: 1= Strongly dislike; 3= No opinion; 5= Strongly like

ElementDescription: How much effort did it take to use the app?
Notes: 1= No effort at all; 3= No opinion; 5= Huge effort

ElementDescription: How good of a fit was the app for people with Fetal Alcohol Spectrum Disorder (FASD) in general?
Notes: 1= Not a good fit at all; 3= No opinion; 5= Excellent fit

ElementDescription: The My Health Coach app improved your overall health and quality of life.
Notes: 1= Strongly disagree; 3= No opinion; 5= Strongly agree

ElementDescription: Did it make sense on how the app was going to help you?
Notes: 1= Very unclear; 3= No opinion; 5= Very clear

ElementDescription: How confident did you feel about your ability to use the My Health Coach app?
Notes: 1= Very unconfident; 3= No opinion; 5= Very confident

ElementDescription: Using the My Health Coach app interfered with other things you had to do.
Notes: 1= Strongly disagree; 3= No opinion; 5= Strongly agree

ElementDescription: Overall, was the My Health Coach app acceptable to you?
Notes: 1= Completely unacceptable; 3= No opinion; 5= Completely acceptable

ElementDescription: Miscellaneous comments on study, interview, methodology relevant to this form data
